iverables are in `output/`, call `submit_done(success=true)` with a short\nsummary of how you solved it.\n\n## Workspace (read-only summary)\n```json\n{\n  \"OBJECTIVE.md\": {\n    \"_file\": \"OBJECTIVE.md\"\n  },\n  \"input\": {\n    \"mk_raw.rds\": {\n      \"_file\": \"mk_raw.rds\"\n    },\n    \"sampleA.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleA.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleB.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleB.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleC.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleC.bismark.cov\"\n    },\n    \"sampleD.bismark.cov\": {\n      \"_file\": \"sampleD.bismark.cov\"\n    }\n  },\n  \"meta.json\": {\n    \"_file\": \"meta.json\"\n  },\n  \"output\": {}\n}\n```\n\nSuccess hint: when `output/unite_stats.tsv` exists under the workspace, you may call submit_done(success=true).\n"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_dOKQcqDM8lj0okRIsaxrSsIb", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"plan\": \"1. Load the `methylKit` library in R.\\n2. Define the list of input files and the treatment vector.\\n3. Use `methRead` to load the bismark coverage files with the specified parameters.\\n4. Use `unite` to combine the methylation data into a single methylBase object.\\n5. Save the united methylBase object to `output/mk_united.rds`.\\n6. Create a summary statistics data frame with the required columns.\\n7. Save the summary statistics to `output/unite_stats.tsv`.\\n8. Verify the existence of the output files and submit the task as done.\"}", "name": "write_plan"}}]}, {"role": "tool", "content": "Wrote plan (527 chars) to .plan.md", "name": "write_plan", "tool_call_id": "call_dOKQcqDM8lj0okRIsaxrSsIb"}, {"role": "assistant", "content": null, "function_call": null, "tool_calls": [{"id": "call_vNpYItfQpATts3ZBpxEe3EFp", "type": "function", "function": {"arguments": "{\"code\": \"library(methylKit)\\n\\n# Define file list and treatment vector\\nfile.list <- list(\\\"input/sampleA.bis